 T-Shirt: Write a function called make_shirt() that accepts a size and the
text of a message that should be printed on the shirt. The function should print
a sentence summarizing the size of the shirt and the message printed on it.
Call the function.

Solution:
code

// Define the make_shirt function
function make_shirt(size: string, message: string): void {
    // Print a sentence summarizing the size of the shirt and the message printed on it
    console.log(`The shirt size is ${size.toUpperCase()} and the message printed on it is: "${message}".`);
}

// Call the function with size "medium" and message "Hello, World!"
make_shirt('medium', 'Hello, World!');







---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
only for reading purpose 
output look like this:
The shirt size is MEDIUM and the message printed on it is: "Hello, World!".

